    <methods>
      <methodStep>
        <description>
          <para>
  Water samples were collected by hand (near surface “grabs” where
  bottles were filled directly) or with a peristaltic pump (various
  depths). In the latter case, Masterflex C-flex tubing was used. Water
  was collected in HDPE or polycarbonate bottles in the field. Samples
  were transported back to the lab and filtered through Geotech 0.45μm
  polyethersulfone capsule filters into acid-washed, ultrapure water
  soaked/rinsed HDPE bottles within 12 hours of collection. Samples were
  stored in coolers during transport and refrigerated until filtration.
  After filtration, samples were frozen (-20 C) until analysis at the
  University of Texas Marine Science Institute, Port Aransas, TX.
  Concentrations of dissolved organic carbon (DOC) and total dissolved
  nitrogen (TDN) were determined using a Shimadzu TOC-V CSH analyzer and
  TNM-1 total nitrogen detector. A 0 - 20 mg/l C/ 0 - 1 mg/l N
  calibration curve was used for river water samples with &gt;5 mg/l C.
  A 0 - 5 mg/l C, 0 - 1 mg/l N calibration curve was used for
  lagoon/ocean water samples and river samples with &lt;5 mg/l C.
</para>
        </description>
      </methodStep>
    </methods>
